 Carlos under pressure
A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: Mohun Bagan officials have put coach Carlos Roberto Pereira under pressure, asking him to improve the teams performance. The officials were learnt to have told the Brazilian during a meeting on Sunday that they were peeved with his substitutions in a few matches as well as inability of creating a strong bench. We just had a chat with him regarding the teams performances, but we are not thinking about removing him, said an official. Mohun Bagan are currently leading the CFL Premier Division table with four matches to go. Meanwhile, Mohammedan Sporting have included Mike Okoro in the squad for Independence Cup in Assam. 
